field.value: 2.04.04. Insert an Image in a Report

field.name: content
field.value:
Several options for adding images in a document are available:

  • Using content widget - allows you just to present an image that is already uploaded in the system
  • Using the image widget - allows you to present an image that is already uploaded in the system and gives you also the abilities to manipulate it
  • Copy and paste image in a document

 

Presenting Image with content widget

Insert an Image in a Report

If you want to insert an image at a Report open the Report in Edit mode by selecting Edit option. At the document page:

  1. Click in the place you want to present the Image
  2. From the document formatting controls select Widgets -> Content Widget

To configure the Widget, in the search screen:

  1. Enter search criteria
  2. Press Search option
  3. Select the Image from the Search result
  4. Press Save button

The Image is displayed in the document.

 

Presenting Image with Image widget

Insert an Image in a Report

If you want to insert an image at a Report open the Report in Edit mode by selecting Edit option. At the document page:

  1. Click in the place you want to present the Image
  2. From the document formatting controls select Widgets -> Image Widget

Note: If the formatting controls aren't visible the tab is locked. To unlock the tab click on the tab and choose the Configure tab.

 

To configure the Widget, in the search screen and the Image is displayed in the document.

Difference between using the Content and Image Widget 

 

The main difference is that when using the Image widget you can perform some actions on the image such as adding annotations, zooming the image etc.

Add Annotations to the Image

In the annotation menu of the image

  1. Select the "Bubble" icon. The "Pencil" icon will be displayed next to it
  2. Select the "Pencil" icon. The Annotation palette will be displayed.
  3. Select one of the options to draw a region from the Annotation palette
  4. Select outline color for the region
  5. Select filled in color for the region
  6. Draw a region on the Image
  7. Add a comment for that annotation
  8. Select Save button

Copy and paste image in a document

The third way to add image in a document is to just copy and paste it on a chosen place in the report. Using this method you can't make any changes to the image as if using the Image Widget.
